sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant User as Usuário
    participant Browser as Browser
    participant Client as App Cliente
    participant Auth as /auth/login
    participant Hosted as HostedAuthenticationAppService
    participant TenantDb as tenant_{id}.OAuthClients
    participant Master as SaasMasterDb

    User->>Client: Abrir área autenticada
    Client->>Client: Gerar state, nonce, code_verifier e code_challenge S256
    Client-->>Browser: Redirect /auth/login + authorization request
    Browser->>Auth: GET /auth/login?response_type=code&tenant_id&client_id&redirect_uri&state&nonce&code_challenge
    Auth->>Hosted: StartAsync(request)
    Hosted->>TenantDb: Buscar OAuthClient ativo por tenant_id/client_id
    TenantDb-->>Hosted: OAuthClient
    Hosted->>Hosted: Validar redirect_uri exato, scopes e PKCE S256
    Hosted->>Master: Criar HostedAuthTransaction + HostedAuthSession

    alt Sem lc_sso válido ou prompt=login
        Auth-->>Browser: Renderizar login hospedado
        Browser->>Auth: POST /auth/login
        Auth->>Hosted: Validar credenciais e 2FA quando necessário
    end

    Hosted->>Master: Criar AuthorizationCodeGrant com code hash e PKCE
    Auth-->>Browser: 302 redirect_uri?code&state
    Browser->>Client: Entregar code e state
    Client->>Client: Validar state
    Client->>Auth: POST /api/auth/token + X-Tenant-Id + code_verifier
    Auth->>Hosted: ExchangeAuthorizationCodeAsync
    Hosted->>Master: Consumir code uma única vez validando PKCE
    Hosted-->>Client: access_token + refresh_token
